## 3. Recommended Risk Mitigation

The delta between the market-implied baseline (complacent) and our fundamental stress test (deteriorating) requires immediate portfolio defensive action.

* **Rotate Out of Lower-Tier Healthcare:** The 7.6% trailing default rate in healthcare providers is accelerating. Liquidate exposure to healthcare facilities carrying high floating-rate debt loads before the market reprices their LGD from 15% to 35%+.
* **Overweight Tech/Quantum Sub-Sectors:** Executive Order 14411 establishes a sovereign tailwind. Maintain aggressively sized 1st lien positions in quantum-adjacent supply chain and AI data center infrastructure, where the 2.2% baseline PD is well-supported by actual cash flows rather than synthetic EBITDA add-backs.
* **Hedge the Spread:** Buy credit protection (via CDX HY) to hedge against the inevitable widening of the 212 bps spread. The market has not fully digested the Warsh Fed's removal of forward guidance.
